Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.textLang: Hebrew; Jewish Babylonian Aramaic (ca. 200-1200 CE); Judeo-Arabic

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 24; written lines: 24; Uniform layout. Complete ruling with hard-point visible. Some folios left blank.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite square script of the 15th century. Superlinear punctuation.
